text: Hey everyone, I'm part of a senior design team at NCSU and our project deals with blockchain and at its core, Hyperledger. We were wondering if anyone has ever deployed fabric onto a network of Raspberry Pis. Thanks for any responses.

Hello <@U35A8J495>, welcome.  I seem to recall someone talking about that before, but I do not know what became of it.  Right now I would guess there would be some basic challenges getting things compiled for ARM where they dont yet exist...we have support for x86_64, ppcle64 and s390x, and would welcome the addition of arm/pi if you wanted to help contribute to that
Any comment on this?  The GRPC thing I mentioned earlier?  Anyone?  Beuler?
